The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves analyzing algorithms and their performance, which falls under data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bayesian priors and expected revenue guarantee suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on revenue maximization, which is a central topic in computational economics (cs.EC).
